official_title: A bill to repeal the act of January 5, 1927, relating to jurisdiction over the taking of fish and game within certain Indian reservations.

summary.text: Repeals the Act making the laws of the state of New York relating to the taking of game and fish applicable to the lands within the Allegheny, Cattaraugus and Oil Spring Indian Reservations.

titles.title: A bill to repeal the act of January 5, 1927, relating to jurisdiction over the taking of fish and game within certain Indian reservations.
